title: PML-N’s Bilal Akbar wins PP-58 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate, Bilal Akbar Khan has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-58, Narowal-V by securing 55,396 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Muhammad Irfan Abid who bagged 45,806 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 51.93%.
